 rigorous than a toy calculator, and intentionally simpler than bespoke legal modeling."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-10 space-y-5","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-panel border border-white/60 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-card backdrop-blur","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-semibold","children":"Funding Rounds as Value Inflection Steps"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-700","children":[["$","p","The model treats each round as an attempt to buy enough time to reach the next value inflection point, not as a generic monthly burn simulation.",{"children":"The model treats each round as an attempt to buy enough time to reach the next value inflection point, not as a generic monthly burn simulation."}],["$","p","Step-up ratio is the key bridge metric: next round pre-money divided by prior round post-money. Weak step-ups increase later down-round and failure risk.",{"children":"Step-up ratio is the key bridge metric: next round pre-money divided by prior round post-money. Weak step-ups increase later down-round and failure risk."}],["$","p","This keeps the simulator aligned with how founders and investors talk about financing trajectories in practice.",{"children":"This keeps the simulator aligned with how founders and investors talk about financing trajectories in practice."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-panel border border-white/60 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-card backdrop-blur","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-semibold","children":"Priced vs Unpriced Rounds"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-700","children":[["$","p","Priced preferred rounds set exact ownership at the moment capital goes in.",{"children":"Priced preferred rounds set exact ownership at the moment capital goes in."}],["$","p","Post-money SAFEs are modeled as future ownership claims that convert on the next qualified financing using cap logic.",{"children":"Post-money SAFEs are modeled as future ownership claims that convert on the next qualified financing using cap logic."}],["$","p","Convertible notes are modeled separately from SAFEs because they accrue interest and stay senior to equity in weak outcomes.",{"children":"Convertible notes are modeled separately from SAFEs because they accrue interest and stay senior to equity in weak outcomes."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-panel border border-white/60 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-card backdrop-blur","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-semibold","children":"Fully Diluted Ownership"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-700","children":[["$","p","The engine always reasons from a fully diluted base so option pool refreshes affect dilution before new-money ownership is assigned.",{"children":"The engine always reasons from a fully diluted base so option pool refreshes affect dilution before new-money ownership is assigned."}],["$","p","Unused pool shares count for dilution math but do not receive proceeds in the exit waterfall.",{"children":"Unused pool shares count for dilution math but do not receive proceeds in the exit waterfall."}],["$","p","This is why employees can experience meaningful dilution even before additional grants are issued.",{"children":"This is why employees can experience meaningful dilution even before additional grants are issued."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-panel border border-white/60 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-card backdrop-blur","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-semibold","children":"Liquidity Waterfalls"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-700","children":[["$","p","Exit value first services note debt and similar senior claims.",{"children":"Exit value first services note debt and similar senior claims."}],["$","p","Preferred stock then chooses either the 1x non-participating preference or as-converted common economics.",{"children":"Preferred stock then chooses either the 1x non-participating preference or as-converted common economics."}],["$","p","Common holders receive the residual, and employee net value is reduced by modeled exercise cost exposure.",{"children":"Common holders receive the residual, and employee net value is reduced by modeled exercise cost exposure."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-panel border border-white/60 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-card backdrop-blur","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-semibold","children":"What v1 Does Not Model"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-700","children":[["$","p","Anti-dilution clauses, warrants, participating preferred, layered seniority, tax treatment, and bespoke governance rights are explained but not simulated numerically.",{"children":"Anti-dilution clauses, warrants, participating preferred, layered seniority, tax treatment, and bespoke governance rights are explained but not simulated numerically."}],["$","p","Those terms can matter a lot, but they push the product from decision-support into bespoke legal modeling.",{"children":"Those terms can matter a lot, but they push the product from decision-support into bespoke legal modeling."}],["$","p","The methodology page should therefore be read as venture math under standard-friendly documents, not as a substitute for counsel.",{"children":"The methodology page should therefore be read as venture math under standard-friendly documents, not as a substitute for counsel."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-10","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-panel border border-white/60 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-card backdrop-blur","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-semibold","children":"Glossary"}],["$","dl",null,{"className":"mt-5 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2","children":[["$